reviewText: Nobody said it had anything to do with the prototype game.  The preview dosn't even suggest it does.  The word "prototype"  was not made up for the game, it has been around long before that and refers to a initial test and or concept model of a potential new object.  Watch the preview and think for yourself.

We writing, arbitrary plot points that make no sense. I had to stop half way through because the narrative stopped making sense to me. I thought this would be a cheeky little adaptation of the [Prototype] video game but I was mislead by the poster. This movie has nothing to do with that but steals from it by the name of the movie and of its protagonist. It's a blatant rip off of Radical's branding for their video game and the creators could honestly be sued for trademark infringement.

TL;DR: Movie has nothing to do with the video game [Prototype]. Story and premise are weak. Avoid unless you need to watch a movie that does narrative pacing, acting, and framing poorly.
